revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
<!-- Categories and interwikis go at the bottom of this page. -->

This template can be used to create a "link note" which can be used to flag an external link for some reason, such as with {{tl|registration required}}. It can add pages to a category to track such links as well. Note that this is an informational template rather than a cleanup tag: for issues which require cleanup, use {{tl|fix}}.

== Usage ==


{{code|<nowiki>{{link note|note=Registration required|cat=Pages containing links or citations to sites that require registration}}</nowiki>}}

The text after "note=" is displayed in the text in parentheses, e.g. {{link note|note=Registration required}}

== See also ==
{{Link notes}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- Categories go here; interwikis go in Wikidata. -->
[[Category:External link note templates]]

}}</includeonly>

